Reasoning: 
1. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) - The paper deals with varieties of finite monoids, which is a topic closely related to formal languages and automata theory. 
2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper uses combinatorics on words, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper involves proving an effective characterization of the join of two varieties, which can be seen as a logical problem. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses omega-terms, which are related to information theory. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves studying the join of two classes of finite monoids, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem.
